  <prompt>
    Run the ADR-030 v2 amendment verification commands documented in the ADR's Operationalization section. Specifically: (1) grep for the `PaneChannel` 5-member union; (2) verify `PaneChannelEventMap` maps `memory` → `MemoryPaneEvent`; (3) verify no `any` payloads in `MemoryPaneEvent`; (4) verify payload field shapes match ADR-030 v2 § "memory channel payload reference" exactly.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform frontend developer. Validating ADR-030 v2 amendment compliance via grep + read.</role>

  <goal>
    Documented confirmation in notes/handoffs/063-adr-030-v2-verification.md that the 4 verification commands pass; ADR-030 v2 amendment compliance verified.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      ADR-030 v2 amendment (the project's own amendment, 2026-06-21) defines the new `memory` channel + payload reference. This task confirms task 060's implementation matches the ADR text byte-for-byte at the type level. Wave 4-A2 runs in parallel with 061 (bus verification), 062 (type-check), 064 (build).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/PaneEventTypes.ts</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-030-pane-event-bus.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-030 v2">5-member closed union; payload fields exactly as specified in amendment § "memory channel payload reference".</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Tier-1 safety: no raw fact text, user message content, recall results in payloads.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Verification only — no code modification.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/architecture/stateful-chat-architecture.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/spec.md</file>
