      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-030-pane-event-bus.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-015-ai-data-governance.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `PaneEventTypes.ts` after task 060's edit. Capture the `PaneChannel` union literal.</step>
    <step order="2">Verify the union contains exactly 5 members: `workspace | context | conversation | safety | memory`. No 6th, no missing 5th.</step>
    <step order="3">Read `MemoryPaneEvent` discriminants. Verify all 5 (`promotion_pending`, `promotion_resolved`, `fact_promoted`, `pin_added`, `pin_removed`) are present.</step>
    <step order="4">For each discriminant, compare field shape against ADR-030 v2 § "memory channel payload reference" (the typescript block). Confirm field names match exactly (case-sensitive).</step>
    <step order="5">Grep `MemoryPaneEvent` definition for `: any` — should be zero hits.</step>
    <step order="6">Grep for tier-1-banned field name patterns inside `MemoryPaneEvent`: `factText`, `userMessage`, `messageContent`, `recallResult`, `fullFact`. Should be zero hits.</step>
    <step order="7">Verify `factSummary` field on `promotion_pending` is typed `string` (no length annotation possible at type-level; runtime enforcement is the dispatch site's job, but document the 80-char cap in code comment if absent — but DO NOT modify here, file as note).</step>
    <step order="8">Document all checks in notes/handoffs/063-adr-030-v2-verification.md as pass/fail table.</step>
    <step order="9">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 063 → ✅.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">PaneEventTypes.ts + ADR-030</tool>
    <tool name="Grep">Field shape + banned tier-1 patterns + union member count</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="docs">notes/handoffs/063-adr-030-v2-verification.md — pass/fail table for 6 checks</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`PaneChannel` 5-member literal verified.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`MemoryPaneEvent` 5 discriminants verified.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All field shapes match ADR text exactly.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Zero `any` types in MemoryPaneEvent.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Zero tier-1-banned field names.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Verification doc filed.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <ui-tests>
    <test scope="grep">String literal validation against ADR text.</test>
  </ui-tests>

  <notes>
    If any check fails, file finding to notes/debug/ — do NOT patch in this task; main session routes to a fix task.
